- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a likely category as the paper mentions the application of the reduction procedure to networks modelling biological systems, which can be seen as control systems. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as automata theory and graph theory, which are relevant to the paper, are subfields of discrete mathematics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the reduction procedure can be seen as a technique for simplifying models used in AI applications. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with formal models and their reduction, which can be seen as a topic related to programming language semantics.
